b'' b'' b'...why did x designers decide to not associate' b'the color with the object being drawn, and instead associate it with the' b'display it is being drawn on?' b'' b'in x10, the drawing attributes were bundled into drawing' b"requests; that is, the server's drawing model was stateless." b'' b'this caused problems with performance and network traffic,' b'so the x11 redesign included the graphic context to codify' b'the drawing state. most application designers who want to' b'draw things in several different colors create a gc for' b'each color during initialization, then pass the gc id in' b'each drawing request.' b'' b"for more information see scheifler and gettys's article" b'in the acm transactions on graphics.' b'' b'' 